ery tool result. Exact records\n   426\tshould be available through drill-down.\n   427\t\n   428\tUseful sections:\n   429\t\n   430\t- Overview\n   431\t- Timeline\n   432\t- Prompts\n   433\t- Claims\n   434\t- Validation\n   435\t- Open Questions\n   436\t- Raw Records\n   437\t\n   438\t`Raw Records` should be secondary. It exists for evidence and debugging, not as\n   439\tthe main review page.\n   440\t\n   441\t## MVP Page Contract\n   442\t\n   \n[TRUNCATED]\nhe branch but did not implement it\n   547\t- turns related only through current branch state\n   548\t\n   549\tThe UI should expose why a turn is highlighted. Reviewers should not have to\n   550\tguess why a session appears.\n   551\t\n   552\t## Privacy And Publication\n   553\t\n   554\tAgent Trail is more sensitive than local handoff because it is meant to be\n   555\topened by colleagues.\n   556\t\n   557\tFor public v1, Agent Trail treats a publicly fetchable `refs/meta/main` as\n   558\talready published metadata. On-demand URL replacement does not grant access to\n   559\tprivate data; it only renders a review page from metadata that is fetchable\n   560\twithout credentials.\n   561\t\n   562\tThere is no Forge-specific public redaction pass in v1. That makes\n   563\t`but-agentlog`'s public/read projection load-bearing. Forge must only render\n   564\trecords returned by that projection; it must not read or render raw internal\n   565\trecords directly.\n   566\t\n   567\tThe rendered data must preserve these `but-agentlog` guarantees:\n   568\t\n   569\t- records must be redacted\n   570\t- local filesystem paths should not be exposed\n   571\t- raw provider session ids should not be exposed\n   572\t- hidden/system/developer prompts should not be exposed\n   573\t- source records should stay bounded and redacted\n   574\t- the user should understand that the trail may contain prompts and tool output\n   575\t\n   576\tIf the required `but-agentlog` public/read projection does not exist yet, build\n   577\tthat before rendering Agent Trail pages from Forge.\n   578\t\n   579\tPublic v1 snapshots should be public but not promoted. Serve them with\n   580\t`noindex` until the publication model is more mature.\n   581\t\n   582\t## Permissions\n   583\t\n   584\tFirst version: public repositories and public metadata only.\n   585\t\n   586\tThe server may generate or show an Agent Trail only when it can access the PR\n   587\tand GitMeta metadata without private credentials. Private repository support\n   588\tshould be a later design pass.\n   589\t\n   590\tFuture policy options:\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:05:14.482Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}